Hmm, I just realized that the different header levels (h1, h2, h3) are complete fan fiction by the vimdoc parser. Vim itself
* only documents `====`  **delimiters** in `:h help-writing`;
* silently accepts `----` delimiters (as the same level!) as well in the syntax file;
* silently highlights SCREAMING CASE as **headings**. (Note that the syntax file does _not_ highlight the actual headings following delimiters, only UPPER CASE lines.)
* and then, of course, there's the dreaded `Column headings ~` which are used for all manner of different things.

Any attempt of generating a consistent hierarchical TOC is bound to fail.
